quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  8,20,"O you who believe, follow God and His messenger, and do not turn away from him when you hear him speak"
  8,21,"Nor be like those who say, “We hear, but do not listen"
  8,22,"For the worst of creatures in the sight of God are the deaf and the dumb, those who understand not"
  8,23,"If God had found in them any good, He would indeed have made them listen. If He had made them listen, they would have turned back and rejected"
  8,24,"O you who believe, respond to God and His messenger when he calls you to that which will give you life, and know that God hovers between a person and his heart, and to Him you all will be gathered"
  8,25,"And be aware of trials which affects not only those of you who do wrong, and know that God is strict in punishment"
  8,26,"Call to mind when you were a small group, despised throughout the land, and afraid that the people might harm you. He provided a safe asylum for you, strengthened you with His aid, and gave you good things for sustenance, that you might be grateful"
  8,27,"O you who believe, do not betray the trust of God and the messenger, nor misappropriate knowingly, things entrusted to you"
  8,28,"And know that your possessions and your progeny are a trial, and that it is God with whom lays your highest reward"